stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> MONITORING

    MONITORING --> DETECTED: hybrid detector finds genuine threshold breach
    MONITORING --> MONITORING: no anomaly / auto-inject keeps demo alive

    DETECTED --> DIAGNOSING: 4-tool MCP agent invoked

    DIAGNOSING --> FIXING: root cause plus validated fix identified, citations attached

    FIXING --> VALIDATING: fix auto-applied, no human approval

    VALIDATING --> OPTIMIZING: telemetry confirmed back within nominal band
    VALIDATING --> ESCALATED: recovery timeout (about 72s safety valve)

    OPTIMIZING --> MONITORING: if 1st occurrence, log only
    OPTIMIZING --> MONITORING: if 2nd+ occurrence, tighten threshold fleet-wide

    ESCALATED --> MONITORING: logged for human engineer

    note right of DETECTED
        Rule-based threshold breach only.
        Statistics alone never trigger a
        full incident (false-positive guard).
    end note

    note right of OPTIMIZING
        Threshold change applies to
        ALL fleet assets, not just
        the one that failed.
    end note
